text: Small outlet for NTUC Fairprice. Variety not as many as other outlet. But it's good to have fair price here for the neighbourhood area.

Small outlet. Nothing much to rave about. Do not have full range for most categories. Out of stocks for some skus are normal. Price is just so so. Customer service is alright. And oh yes, the dumb checkout machine is a pain. It doesnâ€™t really speed up anything just help NTUC to save costs and create unemployment. Also full of clutter at the entrance of the store.
Conveniently located next to the Ayer Rajah Food Centre & Market, serving West Coast residents.

This Fair Price is just a small outlet. They have the basic stuffs but don't expect to find all brands here. Fresh produce in this store are consider fresh. Store a bit small with narrow aisle.  Recent addition of the self check out kiosks makes payment a breeze. Good for a quick pick up for necessities.
A nice supermarket in the area which makes it convenient to shop for groceries. Located near the market and hawker centre. Although the store is small, they do have the essentials stocked up.
